        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName>
                <date>Thurs 4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> day of<lb/> Chanukah&#44; 1854</date>.
            </p>
            <p>To my friend the learned&#44; etc&#44; etc<lb/>
                <addressee>Yitzchok Itzik of the family Leeser</addressee>&#58;</p>
            <p><add>Hebrew</add> Two weeks have passed since I sent<lb/> you a letter to find out how to
                dispatch<lb/> the money&#44; and up to now I have received<lb/> no reply. Moreover&#44; I am
                anxiously await&#8211;<lb/>ing the receipt of the Bible with the English<lb/> translation&#44;
                for I cannot give in to the<lb/> hands of children a Bible translated by<lb/> the
                uncircumcised&#44; for that involves<lb/> a danger of confusing the minds of the<lb/>
                children who will not know where to<lb/> turn&#63; Also be good enough to send me<lb/>
                several prayer books of the Sephardic<lb/> ritual. I expect your answer very
                quickly.<lb/> I hope that you are in good health. Thank<lb/> God for his kindness
                that we are not in<lb/> want. Your <del>expe</del> friend&#44;<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Simon Noht</persName><lb/>
            </p>


        </body>
